224
00:09:18,525 --> 00:09:20,825
     AS MANY TIMES AS WE NEED TO
               TOGETHER, OKAY?  

225
00:09:20,827 --> 00:09:21,993
              OKAY. I'M READY.  

226
00:09:21,995 --> 00:09:23,061
          ARE YOU READY, GARNET?

227
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,196
    I KNOW WHAT SHE'S DOING.    
YOU DO?                         

228
00:09:25,198 --> 00:09:27,499
              STOP!             
     HMM?                       

229
00:09:27,501 --> 00:09:30,201
    IS SOMETHING THE MATTER,    
            AMETHYST?           

230
00:09:30,203 --> 00:09:32,037
      YOU -- YOU SHOULDN'T.     

231
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:35,607
 PEARL, WE SAW YOU.             
                         WHAT?  

232
00:09:35,609 --> 00:09:38,209
YOU NEED TO TELL GARNET         
     IT WAS YOU.                

233
00:09:38,211 --> 00:09:40,011
             I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

234
00:09:40,013 --> 00:09:42,514
           I'M SORRY.           

235
00:09:42,516 --> 00:09:46,885
      IT'S JUST SO MUCH FUN     
    BEING SARDONYX WITH YOU.    

236
00:09:46,887 --> 00:09:50,789
               UH!              
    THAT'S WHY I COULDN'T SEE US
               FINDING PERIDOT. 

237
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,390
WAIT. LET ME EXPLAIN.           

238
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:54,559
     YOU'VE BEEN FIXING THE HUB!

239
00:09:54,561 --> 00:09:56,227
IT REALLY<i> WAS</i> PERIDOT...        

240
00:09:56,229 --> 00:09:57,429
   THE FIRST TIME.              

241
00:09:57,431 --> 00:09:58,930
               YOU TRICKED ME.  

242
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:00,031
 NO. NO, NO, NO, NO.            

243
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:01,866
 NO, WE JUST NEEDED             
  A REASON TO FUSE.             

244
00:10:01,868 --> 00:10:05,270
I JUST WANTED TO SHARE          
A FEW MORE VICTORIES WITH YOU.  

245
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:06,371
        THOSE WEREN'T VICTORIES.

246
00:10:06,373 --> 00:10:07,639
     Amethyst: WAIT, GARNET.    

247
00:10:07,641 --> 00:10:09,908
               YOU KNOW, WE'RE  
        SO MUCH WEAKER THAN YOU.

248
00:10:09,910 --> 00:10:12,744
         FUSING WITH YOU IS LIKE
       OUR ONE CHANCE TO FEEL...

249
00:10:12,746 --> 00:10:13,945
                  STRONGER.     

250
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:14,946
    Garnet: DON'T DEFEND HER.   

251
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,581
             PERIDOT            
     IS OUT THERE SOMEWHERE,    

252
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:19,618
 AND PEARL'S BEEN DISTRACTING US
          WITH NOTHING.         

253
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:22,220
   GARNET...                    
         THAT'S ENOUGH.         

254
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:24,122
     AMETHYST, FUSE WITH ME.    

255
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:25,156
                   BUT...       

256
00:10:25,158 --> 00:10:27,959
 LET'S JUST GET THIS OVER WITH. 

257
00:10:44,111 --> 00:10:46,411
             <i> PLEASE FORGIVE ME.</i>

258
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:48,446
<i> OF COURSE I FORGIVE YOU.</i>       

259
00:10:48,448 --> 00:10:51,349
         [<i> BOTH CRYING</i> ]        

260
00:11:01,928 --> 00:11:03,428
        MAN.                    

261
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:04,929
IT SURE WOULD BE NICE           

262
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:07,799
IF THINGS WORKED OUT            
THE WAY THEY DO IN CARTOONS.    

263
00:11:07,801 --> 00:11:09,000
                    YEAH.       

264
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:11,436
      IT WOULD.                 

265
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:15,006
             ♪ YOU ♪            

266
00:11:16,376 --> 00:11:20,211
        ♪ LOVE LIKE YOU ♪       

267
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:31,122
    PEARL! WHERE'VE YOU BEEN?   

268
00:11:31,124 --> 00:11:33,124
        EH. LOOKING FOR PERIDOT.

269
00:11:33,126 --> 00:11:34,993
        FOR A FEW DAYS STRAIGHT.

270
00:11:34,995 --> 00:11:37,162
               STEVEN, I KNOW   
               I MIGHT HAVE...  

271
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:39,330
        DISAPPOINTED ALL OF YOU.

272
00:11:39,332 --> 00:11:41,032
               I KNOW GARNET'S  
             VERY UPSET WITH ME.

273
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:43,968
   BUT I'M GOING TO PROVE TO HER
   THAT SHE CAN TRUST ME AGAIN. 

274
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:47,005
                 OH, GARNET!    
 I WAS JUST LOOKING FOR PERIDOT!

275
00:11:47,007 --> 00:11:50,308
  SHE'S BOUND TO BE SOMEWHERE,  
             RIGHT?             

276
00:11:50,310 --> 00:11:51,876
         ANY NEW IDEAS?         

277
00:11:55,315 --> 00:11:57,148
           I'M SORRY.           

278
00:11:57,150 --> 00:12:02,153
WHO WANTS TO GO ON A ROAD TRIP?!

279
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,657
    UM...IS THIS A BAD TIME?    

280
00:12:05,659 --> 00:12:07,258
      NO. PLEASE CONTINUE.      

281
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:09,661
WELL, I GOTTA DRIVE OVER TO     
THE NEXT STATE, KEYSTONE.       

282
00:12:09,663 --> 00:12:10,995
            YOU MEAN,           
       THE KEYSTONE STATE?      

283
00:12:10,997 --> 00:12:12,897
  RIGHT, THE STATE              
  NAMED KEYSTONE.               

284
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:15,166
I MET A GUY ON AN INTERNET      
    MESSAGE BOARD               

285
00:12:15,168 --> 00:12:17,769
WHO'S SELLING CAR-WASH          
BRUSHES FOR REAL CHEAP!         

286
00:12:17,771 --> 00:12:20,338
I JUST GOTTA MEET HIM IN        
KEYSTONE AND PICK 'EM UP.       

287
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:23,842
  I DON'T LIKE THOSE BRUSHES.   
  THEY FEEL WEIRD ON YOUR FUR.  

288
00:12:23,844 --> 00:12:26,845
WELL, DO YOU LIKE MOTELS?       
                     PROBABLY!  

289
00:12:26,847 --> 00:12:29,247
 THINK YOU'D LIKE TO            
   STAY AT A MOTEL              

290
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:30,615
WITH YOUR FAVORITE DAD?         

291
00:12:30,617 --> 00:12:33,251
     I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'RE     
         MY FAVORITE...         

292
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:34,786
     WHAT? HUH?                 

293
00:12:34,788 --> 00:12:36,721
   OH, YOU KIDDER.              
     COME HERE.                 

294
00:12:36,723 --> 00:12:38,623
       I CAN'T WAIT TO GET      
          ROOM SERVICE!         

295
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:41,359
YOU'RE THINKING OF A<i> HOTEL.</i>     

296
00:12:41,361 --> 00:12:43,027
   WE'RE GOING TO               
      A<i> MOTEL!</i>                  

297
00:12:43,029 --> 00:12:45,563
  IT'LL HAVE A POOL             
    AND FREE ICE.               

298
00:12:45,565 --> 00:12:49,601
AND IT'S RIGHT NEXT TO          
THE BEST DINER IN THE WORLD!    

299
00:12:49,603 --> 00:12:51,870
                I'M COMING, TOO.
    WHAT?                       

300
00:12:51,872 --> 00:12:53,471
                  [ GASPS ]     
                EVEN BETTER!    

301
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:56,040
HEY, GARNET, I KNOW I'M         
TALKING THIS PLACE UP,          

302
00:12:56,042 --> 00:12:58,143
BUT IT AIN'T EXACTLY            
      THE RITZ.                 

303
00:12:58,145 --> 00:12:59,811
      I'LL BE THE JUDGE OF THAT.

304
00:12:59,813 --> 00:13:03,281
WELL, IN THAT CASE...           
     ROAD TRIP!                 

305
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:04,482
                 ROAD TRIP!     

306
00:13:04,484 --> 00:13:06,151
           ROAD TRIP.           

307
00:13:06,153 --> 00:13:07,552
     WONDERFUL!                 

308
00:13:07,554 --> 00:13:09,487
I'LL MAKE SURE AMETHYST         
KNOWS THAT... [ SIGHS ]         

309
00:13:09,489 --> 00:13:11,089
              FINE.             

310
00:13:11,091 --> 00:13:13,158
         WELL, GOODBYE.         

311
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,960
           THIS IS GONNA BE FUN,
                 RIGHT, DAD?    

312
00:13:17,898 --> 00:13:19,631
     [ SNORING ]                

313
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:22,734
                  [ YAWNS ]     

314
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:29,574
             ANOTHER GREAT THING
               ABOUT MOTELS --  

315
00:13:29,576 --> 00:13:32,577
          YOU CAN DRIVE RIGHT UP
                TO YOUR DOOR!   

316
00:13:32,579 --> 00:13:34,245
            [ GASPS ]           

317
00:13:34,247 --> 00:13:37,749
I'M GONNA SWIM IN THE POOL,     
ORDER A MOVIE, GET FREE ICE!    

318
00:13:37,751 --> 00:13:39,083
      IT'S GONNA BE GREAT!      

319
00:13:39,085 --> 00:13:42,787
NOT BEFORE WE CHECK FOR BEDBUGS,
            IT ISN'T!           

320
00:13:42,789 --> 00:13:45,323
               MM.              

321
00:13:45,325 --> 00:13:46,858
                 GOOD NEWS!     
               WE'RE BUGLESS!   

322
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:49,027
             [ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
             OOP, THAT'S MY CUE.

323
00:13:49,029 --> 00:13:51,996
   HEY, DO YOU MIND HOLDING DOWN
      THE FORT TILL I GET BACK? 

324
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,668
   GREAT. I'M OFF TO SEE A MAN  
      ABOUT A TUNNEL BRUSH.     

325
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:59,204
        AN INTERNET MAN.        

326
00:13:59,206 --> 00:14:03,208
   IF I'M NOT BACK IN AN HOUR,  
        CALL THE POLICE.        

327
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,176
                   OH-KAY!      

328
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:07,779
         BOUNCE WITH ME, GARNET!
                [ GRUNTING ]    

329
00:14:07,781 --> 00:14:09,814
                O-OR WE COULD   
             LOOK AT BROCHURES. 

330
00:14:09,816 --> 00:14:12,116
          OOH, KEYSTONE CAVERNS.

331
00:14:12,118 --> 00:14:13,218
     CALM DOWN.                 

332
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:14,853
            [ PANTS ]           

333
00:14:14,855 --> 00:14:17,388
        I DON'T FEEL LIKE       
        FORGIVING PEARL!        

334
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,224
       DON'T UNDERSTAND --      
            WE MUST!            

335
00:14:19,226 --> 00:14:21,960
 IF YOU'RE NOT GOING TO LISTEN, 
      THEN YOU CAN JUST GO!     

336
00:14:21,962 --> 00:14:22,961
              AAH!              

337
00:14:22,963 --> 00:14:24,696
  WE MUST MOVE PAST THIS, RUBY. 

338
00:14:24,698 --> 00:14:27,465
   SHE LIED TO US               
SO WE'D FORM SARDONYX!          

339
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:30,735
   SHE TRICKED US!              
DON'T YOU FEEL USED?!           

340
00:14:30,737 --> 00:14:32,737
         RUBY! SAPPHIRE!        
              I --              

341
00:14:32,739 --> 00:14:34,839
             YOU'RE CHOOSING TO 
             TAKE IT PERSONALLY.

342
00:14:34,841 --> 00:14:36,975
IT'S FUSION, SAPPHIRE!          

343
00:14:36,977 --> 00:14:40,745
WHAT'S MORE PERSONAL TO US      
    THAN FUSION?!               

344
00:14:40,747 --> 00:14:43,147
      I KNOW YOU'RE STILL UPSET.

345
00:14:43,149 --> 00:14:44,649
OH, SO IT'S JUST ME?            

346
00:14:44,651 --> 00:14:45,984
               OF COURSE NOT.   

347
00:14:45,986 --> 00:14:50,321
    CAN'T YOU SEE I'M COMPLETELY
            ENGULFED WITH RAGE? 

348
00:14:50,323 --> 00:14:52,490
WELL, IT DOESN'T FEEL LIKE IT!  

349
00:14:52,492 --> 00:14:54,058
    THE SOONER WE FORGIVE PEARL,

350
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:56,261
           THE BETTER IT WILL BE
                 FOR US ALL.    

351
00:14:56,263 --> 00:15:00,498
YOU'RE NOT AS ABOVE THIS        
AS YOU THINK YOU ARE!           

352
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,000
     [ GRUNTS ]                 

353
00:15:02,002 --> 00:15:04,102
           YES, I AM.           

354
00:15:04,104 --> 00:15:05,904
    [ GRUNTING ]                

355
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:10,508
      YOU CAN'T STAY ANGRY      
        WITH HER FOREVER.       

356
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:11,609
     WANNA BET?                 

357
00:15:11,611 --> 00:15:13,378
              RUBY, THE CARPET. 

358
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:16,247
   YOU -- I CAN'T EVEN -- UGH!  

359
00:15:16,249 --> 00:15:17,382
         [ DOOR SLAMS ]         

360
00:15:17,384 --> 00:15:21,185
          NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN?

361
00:15:21,187 --> 00:15:23,755
NICE TO SEE YOU, TOO.           

362
00:15:23,757 --> 00:15:26,724
      [ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]     

363
00:15:26,726 --> 00:15:29,527
     HEY, RUBY.                 

364
00:15:29,529 --> 00:15:31,095
YOU WANNA SWIM IN THE POOL?     

365
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:32,630
            IT'S FUSION, STEVEN!

366
00:15:32,632 --> 00:15:34,299
             IT'S LIKE SAPPHIRE 
             DOESN'T EVEN CARE! 

367
00:15:34,301 --> 00:15:37,201
       AND WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE 
      THE BIGGER GEM ABOUT THIS.

368
00:15:37,203 --> 00:15:39,871
                WE'RE<i> ALWAYS</i>    
               THE BIGGER GEM!  

369
00:15:39,873 --> 00:15:42,941
            WELL, NOT THIS TIME!
               NOT ABOUT THIS!  

370
00:15:42,943 --> 00:15:46,544
COME ON, WHY DON'T YOU COME     
COOL DOWN IN THE POOL?          

371
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:49,714
   I DON'T NEED TO COOL DOWN!   

372
00:15:49,716 --> 00:15:53,284
   COME ON, RUBY.               
  THE WATER'S NICE!             

373
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:57,722
    WHY DOES SHE ALWAYS ACT LIKE
          I'M BEING RIDICULOUS? 

374
00:15:57,724 --> 00:15:59,290
          JUST BECAUSE SHE WANTS
                 TO PRETEND     

375
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,159
              THAT SHE DOESN'T  
              HAVE FEELINGS?!   

376
00:16:01,161 --> 00:16:02,293
      UH, RUBY?                 

377
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:03,661
                [ GRUMBLING ]   

378
00:16:03,663 --> 00:16:05,730
YOU MADE A WARM SPOT!           

379
00:16:05,732 --> 00:16:08,066
   AH! A HOT SPOT!              

380
00:16:08,068 --> 00:16:09,667
      BOILING!                  

381
00:16:09,669 --> 00:16:10,969
      [ GASPS ]                 

382
00:16:10,971 --> 00:16:14,839
UH, I'M GONNA GO BACK           
    TO THE ROOM.                

383
00:16:14,841 --> 00:16:16,741
           [ SHIVERS ]          

384
00:16:16,743 --> 00:16:18,409
            SAPPHIRE?           

385
00:16:18,411 --> 00:16:19,510
         HELLO, STEVEN.         

386
00:16:19,512 --> 00:16:22,647
          A-ARE YOU...          
         D-D-DOIN' OKAY?        

387
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:25,116
            I'M FINE.           

388
00:16:25,118 --> 00:16:27,318
             O-OKAY.            

389
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,153
      W-WANNA WATCH TV TOGETHER?

390
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:30,922
        SURE.                   

391
00:16:30,924 --> 00:16:33,758
          HUH. THE CHANNELS ARE 
          ALL THE WRONG NUMBERS.

392
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,960
           HEY, CAN YOU USE YOUR
                FUTURE POWERS   

393
00:16:35,962 --> 00:16:38,663
         TO PREDICT WHAT CHANNEL
             I'D LOVE THE MOST? 

394
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:42,433
      HMM...43.                 
BUT THERE'S NOT MUCH ON.        

395
00:16:42,435 --> 00:16:46,270
       [ CHANGES CHANNEL ]      

396
00:16:46,272 --> 00:16:47,605
              HEY, SAPPHIRE...  

397
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:49,941
    EVEN IF I DO,               
 RUBY WON'T LISTEN.             

398
00:16:49,943 --> 00:16:51,142
                    HUH?        

399
00:16:51,144 --> 00:16:53,478
 YOU'RE GOING TO SAY            
I SHOULD TALK TO RUBY,          

400
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,213
 BUT IT WON'T HELP.             

401
00:16:55,215 --> 00:16:58,182
               B-BUT SHE SEEMS  
                REALLY UPSET.   

402
00:16:58,184 --> 00:16:59,450
THAT DOESN'T MATTER.            

403
00:16:59,452 --> 00:17:01,619
  WE CAN'T STAY MAD             
  AT PEARL FOREVER,             

404
00:17:01,621 --> 00:17:03,454
AND SHE CAN'T STAY MAD          
   AT ME FOREVER.               

405
00:17:03,456 --> 00:17:06,357
AND THEN SHE'LL COME BACK       
AND SEE THAT I'M RIGHT.         

406
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:08,626
       A-A-ARE YOU S-SURE?      

407
00:17:08,628 --> 00:17:12,964
I CAN SEE THE PATH OF FATE AS IT
  STRETCHES TOWARD THE HORIZON. 

408
00:17:12,966 --> 00:17:14,866
        RUBY CAN'T AVOID        
        THE INEVITABLE.         

409
00:17:14,868 --> 00:17:17,702
 SHE'S JUST LETTING HER EMOTIONS
        GET OUT OF HAND.        

410
00:17:17,704 --> 00:17:19,670
      N-N-NOT YOU, THOUGH?      

411
00:17:19,672 --> 00:17:21,672
               NO.              

412
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:23,841
               I'M...GOING TO   
               THE BATHROOM.    

413
00:17:23,843 --> 00:17:25,810
        ALSO INEVITABLE.        

414
00:17:25,812 --> 00:17:27,512
                UH, SAPPHIRE?   

415
00:17:27,514 --> 00:17:29,647
            THE TOILET'S FROZEN.

416
00:17:29,649 --> 00:17:31,249
          SUCH IS FATE.         

417
00:17:31,251 --> 00:17:34,185
       AM I FATED TO PEE OUTSIDE
             ON THE GRASS, TOO? 

418
00:17:34,187 --> 00:17:35,720
              YES.              

419
00:17:35,722 --> 00:17:37,488
       "KEYSTONE STATE"...      

420
00:17:39,659 --> 00:17:42,326
               HEY, STU-BALL,   
              I BROUGHT DINNER. 

421
00:17:42,328 --> 00:17:44,162
HEY, DAD. HOW'D IT GO?          

422
00:17:44,164 --> 00:17:47,398
WELL, HE WASN'T AN AXE MURDERER,
              SO THAT WAS GOOD. 

423
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,734
      WHAT ARE YOU DOING OUTSIDE
          IN YOUR BATHING SUIT? 

424
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:51,235
             AND WHERE'S GARNET?

425
00:17:51,938 --> 00:17:54,872
     HE'S NOT GOING TO LIKE     
        THAT IT'S SQUARE.       

426
00:17:54,874 --> 00:17:57,442
                  OH, BOY.      
          WHERE'S THE OTHER ONE?

427
00:17:57,444 --> 00:18:01,245
SHE'S PACING AROUND IN          
WHAT USED TO BE THE POOL.       

428
00:18:03,183 --> 00:18:05,516
        SOMETHING PRETTY SERIOUS
              MUST BE GOING ON  

429
00:18:05,518 --> 00:18:06,751
     IF IT MADE GARNET SPLIT UP.

430
00:18:06,753 --> 00:18:09,253
      BUT HEY, WE CAN STILL HAVE
                A GOOD TIME.    

431
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:11,122
   SQUARE PIZZA?!               

432
00:18:11,124 --> 00:18:13,357
WHAT'S WRONG WITH THIS          
    CRAZY STATE?!               

433
00:18:13,359 --> 00:18:15,860
       SON, THERE'LL COME A TIME
                IN YOUR LIFE    

434
00:18:15,862 --> 00:18:18,196
        WHEN YOU LEARN TO ACCEPT
                 ALL PIZZA.     

435
00:18:18,198 --> 00:18:21,933
WHY CAN'T RUBY AND SAPPHIRE     
    JUST MAKE UP?               

436
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:23,901
           SOMETIMES PEOPLE THAT
               LOVE EACH OTHER  

437
00:18:23,903 --> 00:18:26,304
  CAN HURT EACH OTHER'S FEELINGS
            WITHOUT MEANING TO. 

438
00:18:26,306 --> 00:18:28,473
        WE SHOULD JUST GIVE THEM
                 SOME SPACE.    

439
00:18:28,475 --> 00:18:29,907
BUT I THINK THEY'D WORK IT OUT  

440
00:18:29,909 --> 00:18:31,609
   IF THEY'D JUST               
 TALK TO EACH OTHER.            

441
00:18:31,611 --> 00:18:33,478
       EVERYTHING WILL BE BETTER
               IN THE MORNING.  

442
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,580
               WE'LL ALL GO TO  
    THE BEST DINER IN THE WORLD,

443
00:18:35,582 --> 00:18:38,082
      WHERE THEY'LL EAT THE BEST
        BREAKFAST IN THE WORLD. 

444
00:18:38,084 --> 00:18:39,717
YOU THINK THAT'LL HELP?         

445
00:18:39,719 --> 00:18:42,887
 NOTHING LIKE A LITTLE BREAKFAST
      TO BRING PEOPLE TOGETHER. 

446
00:18:42,889 --> 00:18:46,090
   YOU REALLY ARE               
  MY FAVORITE DAD.              

447
00:18:46,092 --> 00:18:48,559
         I KNEW THIS PIZZA WOULD
           PUT ME OVER THE TOP. 

448
00:18:49,729 --> 00:18:52,763
                [ WHISTLING ]   
                    HEY!        

449
00:18:52,765 --> 00:18:54,298
     THANK YOU.                 

450
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:55,399
                   THANKS!      

451
00:18:58,738 --> 00:19:00,738
             WHAT'S THE MATTER? 
                 NOT HUNGRY?    

452
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:02,773
                 GEMS DON'T     
              NEED TO EAT, DAD. 

453
00:19:02,775 --> 00:19:05,843
        EH, GARNET LIKES        
        TO EAT SOMETIMES.       

454
00:19:05,845 --> 00:19:09,313
        UGH!                    
WELL, GARNET'S NOT HERE!        

455
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:14,519
              MMM.              
            OH, BOY!            

456
00:19:14,521 --> 00:19:19,157
               THIS REALLY IS   
    THE BEST DINER IN THE WORLD!

457
00:19:20,527 --> 00:19:22,426
       YOU'RE SHAKING THE TABLE.

458
00:19:22,428 --> 00:19:23,694
      OH?! HEH!                 

459
00:19:23,696 --> 00:19:26,764
I'M KINDA SURPRISED YOU FELT    
ANYTHING AT ALL, TO BE HONEST!  

460
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:29,433
        I DIDN'T<i> NEED</i> TO FEEL --
                   I SAW.       

461
00:19:29,435 --> 00:19:35,006
EVERYTHING'S JUST SO CRYSTAL    
CLEAR TO YOU, ISN'T IT?!        

462
00:19:36,109 --> 00:19:37,441
         THIS WILL PASS.        

463
00:19:37,443 --> 00:19:39,944
     SHE'LL EVENTUALLY JUST     
        BURN HERSELF OUT.       

464
00:19:39,946 --> 00:19:41,112
THAT'S WHAT YOU THINK!          

465
00:19:41,114 --> 00:19:44,048
  I AM AN ETERNAL FLAME, BABY!  

466
00:19:46,319 --> 00:19:47,718
           [ GASPS ]            
YOU DON'T KNOW ME!              

467
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:48,953
           [ ARGUING ]          

468
00:19:48,955 --> 00:19:51,622
Greg: HEY, IT'S OKAY, PAL!      

469
00:19:51,624 --> 00:19:52,957
     WE CAN STILL SAVE THIS!    

470
00:19:52,959 --> 00:19:55,293
 WHY DON'T WE JUST BAG THESE UP 
          TO GO AND --          

471
00:19:57,697 --> 00:19:59,363
            AH, GEEZ.           

472
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:02,800
          Both: STEVEN!         

473
00:20:02,802 --> 00:20:04,235
 I WAS SO HAPPY WHEN GARNET SAID

474
00:20:04,237 --> 00:20:06,637
 SHE WAS GONNA COME ON THIS TRIP
        WITH ME AND DAD!        

475
00:20:06,639 --> 00:20:09,140
       HOME'S BEEN AWFUL.       
       HERE'S BEEN AWFUL!       

476
00:20:09,142 --> 00:20:11,642
     I THOUGHT YOU WANTED TO    
        HAVE A FUN TIME,        

477
00:20:11,644 --> 00:20:14,045
       BUT EVERYONE'S BEEN      
       ACTING AWFUL, TOO!       

478
00:20:14,047 --> 00:20:15,513
   IT -- IT JUST CAME WITH US.  

479
00:20:15,515 --> 00:20:20,218
       I DON'T UNDERSTAND.      
       IS IT -- IS IT ME?       

480
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:22,353
NO! STEVEN, IT'S ALL US!        

481
00:20:22,355 --> 00:20:25,656
           BUT WE MADE HIM FEEL 
          LIKE IT WAS HIS FAULT.

482
00:20:25,658 --> 00:20:27,558
 I KEEP LOOKING INTO THE FUTURE 

483
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,661
      WHEN ALL OF THIS HAS      
      ALREADY BEEN SOLVED,      

484
00:20:30,663 --> 00:20:34,498
     AS IF IT DOESN'T MATTER    
  HOW YOU FEEL IN THE PRESENT.  

485
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:38,236
 [ Crying ] NO WONDER YOU THINK 
          I DON'T CARE!         

486
00:20:38,238 --> 00:20:39,036
            SAPPHIRE!           

487
00:20:39,038 --> 00:20:40,705
 NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!            

488
00:20:40,707 --> 00:20:42,106
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT!           

489
00:20:42,108 --> 00:20:43,608
I-I DIDN'T WANT TO LOOK FOR     
     A SOLUTION.                

490
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:44,709
I JUST WANTED TO BE MAD.        

491
00:20:44,711 --> 00:20:46,944
    YOU'RE RIGHT.               
YOU'RE ALWAYS RIGHT.            

492
00:20:46,946 --> 00:20:48,179
 I WAS BEING STUPID.            

493
00:20:48,181 --> 00:20:50,715
    I DON'T THINK YOU'RE STUPID!

494
00:20:50,717 --> 00:20:53,351
           I'M SORRY.           

495
00:20:53,353 --> 00:20:58,189
      YOU HONESTLY THINK I'M NOT
      UPSET ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED?

496
00:20:58,191 --> 00:21:02,026
         I WAS JUST TRYING TO DO
              THE RIGHT THING.  

497
00:21:02,028 --> 00:21:05,029
         I KNOW.                
                     [ SIGHS ]  

498
00:21:05,031 --> 00:21:08,532
YOU KNOW WHAT'S NICE ABOUT      
   BEING SPLIT UP?              

499
00:21:08,534 --> 00:21:09,800
                    WHAT?       

500
00:21:09,802 --> 00:21:11,969
I GET TO LOOK AT YOU.           

501
00:21:11,971 --> 00:21:14,538
                    PFFT!       
                 [ LAUGHS ]     

502
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:15,973
                 BE SERIOUS!    

503
00:21:15,975 --> 00:21:17,608
THERE'S MY LAFFY SAFFY!         

504
00:21:17,610 --> 00:21:19,977
     SHH! YOU'RE EMBARRASSING ME
            IN FRONT OF STEVEN! 

505
00:21:19,979 --> 00:21:24,282
        [ BOTH GIGGLING ]       

506
00:21:29,389 --> 00:21:31,322
            [ SIGHS ]           

507
00:21:31,324 --> 00:21:32,990
WELL, I PAID FOR BREAKFAST...   

508
00:21:32,992 --> 00:21:35,126
  AND THE DAMAGE TO THE BOOTH.  

509
00:21:35,128 --> 00:21:37,828
       ANYHOO, I THINK I'M      
       ALL VACATIONED OUT.      

510
00:21:37,830 --> 00:21:39,497
     READY TO CALL IT A DAY?    

511
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:44,402
 NOT BEFORE WE GET OUR FREE ICE!

512
00:21:44,404 --> 00:21:45,603
             GARNET!            

513
00:21:45,605 --> 00:21:48,472
           WE'RE HOME!          

514
00:21:48,474 --> 00:21:50,908
 I JUST DON'T KNOW WHY I KEEP --
               OH!              

515
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:52,743
 YOU LOOK LIKE YOU ALL HAD FUN. 

516
00:21:52,745 --> 00:21:55,279
    YEAH, IT ALL WORKED OUT!    

517
00:21:55,281 --> 00:21:57,281
      GARNET, HOW ARE YOU?      

518
00:21:57,283 --> 00:21:58,649
            NOT NOW.            

519
00:22:00,019 --> 00:22:03,354
      SHE'S SPEAKING TO ME      
        AGAIN...KIND OF.        

520
00:22:03,356 --> 00:22:05,456
         THAT REALLY WAS        
          A GREAT TRIP.         

521
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:07,325
      [ GASPS ]                 
   CAN WE GO BACK?              

522
00:22:07,327 --> 00:22:10,828
              MAYBE ONE DAY...  
          BUT NOT TO THAT DINER.

523
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:13,097
                  OH, BOY.      

524
00:22:15,635 --> 00:22:19,770
 [ CLOSING THEME MUSIC PLAYING ]

